itemDescription: judge of the High Court of Justice and lawyer from Nova Scotia

wikipedia_page.main: Sir Thomas Dickson Archibald (1817 — 1876) was judge of the High Court of Justice (Common Pleas Division) and lawyer from Nova Scotia. He served from 6 February 1875 until 1 November 1875.

link_mentions.page: List of High Court judges of England and Wales

response: Thomas Dickson Archibald (8 April 1813 – 18 October 1890) was a Canadian  businessman and politician.
* 18 October – Sir Thomas Dickson Archibald, judge (born 1817 in Nova Scotia)
